.TH seed 1  "seed " 
.SH NAME
seed \- Pre\-load a gene\-bank with known\-working techniques (per\-WAF or per\-host)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBseed\fR [\fB\-\-technique\fR] [\fB\-\-waf\fR] [\fB\-\-host\fR] [\fB\-\-proxy\-bank\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Pre\-load a gene\-bank with known\-working techniques (per\-WAF or per\-host)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-technique\fR \fI<TECHNIQUE>...\fR
Comma\-separated technique pool keys to seed. Each key is a string like `EncodingDoubleUrl`, `GrammarTautology`, `SmugglingClTeBasic`. Run `wafrift techniques list` for the canonical list
.TP
\fB\-\-waf\fR \fI<WAF>\fR
Seed the per\-WAF GeneBank under `~/.wafrift/genomes/<waf>.json`. Mutually exclusive with `\-\-host`
.TP
\fB\-\-host\fR \fI<HOST>\fR
Seed the proxy gene\-bank for a specific host. Mutually exclusive with `\-\-waf`
.TP
\fB\-\-proxy\-bank\fR \fI<PROXY_BANK>\fR
Override the proxy gene\-bank path. Default `~/.wafrift/gene\-bank.json`. Only consulted when `\-\-host` is set
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show what would be written and exit 0 without touching disk
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
